SUMMARY:Deadline: Rodger and Joann McLennan Canadian War Art Research Fello
 wship 2026
DESCRIPTION:The National Gallery of Canada's Rodger and Joann McLennan Cana
 dian War Art Research Fellowship encourages and supports advanced research
  in Canadian and Indigenous Canadian war and military art. Research must r
 elate to any aspect of Canadian war or military art (including painting\, 
 drawing\, sculpture\, photography\, printmaking\, and other media) and mus
 t emphasise the use and investigation of the collections of the National G
 allery of Canada\, the Canadian War Museum\, and Library and Archives Cana
 da. The Fellowship supports original research by scholars undertaking publ
 ishing\, exhibition\, thesis\, and dissertation work or their equivalents.
  AMOUNT: up to $5\,000\, including expenses and/or stipend. TENURE: one ca
 lendar year beginning 1 September 2026\; tenable only at the National Gall
 ery of Canada. ELIGIBILITY: open to art historians\, curators\, critics\, 
 conservators\, graduate students\, and independent or other professionals 
 working in the visual arts\, museology\, and related disciplines in the hu
 manities and social sciences\; international applicants welcome. Researche
 rs from outside Canada must ensure all visa requirements and documentation
  are in order before entry and the start of the Fellowship. Applications a
 re invited from all qualified candidates\, including Indigenous peoples\, 
 women\, people of any sexual orientation\, gender identity or gender expre
 ssion\, racialized people\, and people with disabilities. TO APPLY: submit
  a complete application in English or French as a single PDF by email to A
 my Rose\, Senior Manager\, Library\, Archives and Research Fellowship Prog
 ram\, at erefel@gallery.ca. Deadline: 26 June 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Natio
 nal Gallery of Canada\nLocation: Ottawa\, Canada\; tenable only at the Nat
 ional Gallery of Canada.\nAward: Up to $5\,000 (including expenses and/or 
 stipend). No application fee.\nDuration: One calendar year\, beginning 1 S
 eptember 2026.\n\nMore: https://www.gallery.ca/research/fellowships/rodger
 -and-joann-mclennan-canadian-war-art-fellowship
URL:https://www.gallery.ca/research/fellowships/rodger-and-joann-mclennan-c
 anadian-war-art-fellowship
LOCATION:Ottawa\, Canada\; tenable only at the National Gallery of Canada.
